{"title": "Some Problems of Philosophy", "description": "For several years before his death Professor William James cherished the purpose of stating his views on certain problems of metaphysics in a book addressed particularly to readers of philosophy.  He began the actual writing of this 'introductory text-book for students in metaphysics,' as he once called it, in March, 1909, and to complete it was at last his dearest ambition.  But illness, and other demands on his diminished strength, continued to interfere, and what is now published is all that he had succeeded in writing when he died in August, 1910. - Summary by Henry James, Jr.", "duration": 17267, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "942", "name": "William James"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/some_problems_of_philosophy_pjt_1503_librivox/Philosophy_1503.jpg", "copyright_year": "1916", "genres": ["Philosophy"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "P. J. Taylor"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "P. J. Taylor"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Larry Wilson"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Chapter I - Philosophy and Its Critics", "readers": [9165], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/some_problems_of_philosophy_pjt_1503_librivox/problemsphilosophy_01_james_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1934}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter II - The Problems of Metaphysics", "readers": [9165], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/some_problems_of_philosophy_pjt_1503_librivox/problemsphilosophy_02_james_64kb.mp3", "duration": 655}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter III - The Problem of Being", "readers": [9165], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/some_problems_of_philosophy_pjt_1503_librivox/problemsphilosophy_03_james_64kb.mp3", "duration": 685}, {"section": 4, "title": "Chapter IV - Percept and Concept - The Import of Concepts", "readers": [9165], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/some_problems_of_philosophy_pjt_